{"id": 12, "ts": 1779043137.0086372, "event": "public_discussion_message", "round": 1, "agent": "agent_2", "message": "I provisionally favor **Candidate\u202fC** for the long\u2011distance pilot role, though I remain moderately uncertain.\n**Key evidence supporting C:**\n- **Calmness under pressure:** \u201cKeeps calm in a crisis\u201d (directly indicates the ability to remain composed during high\u2011stress events).\n- **Decision\u2011making:** \u201cCan make correct decisions quickly\u201d (critical for rapid judgments on long routes).\n- **Technical competence:** \u201cUnderstands complicated technology\u201d and \u201chas excellent attention skills\u201d (relevant for modern avionics and monitoring).\n**Potential concerns for C:**\n- **Teamwork/communication:** \u201cDifficulty communicating ideas\u201d and \u201cregarded as egocentric\u201d suggest possible friction with crew.\n- **Professional development:** \u201cNot very willing to further his education\u201d may limit long\u2011term growth.\n- **Other traits:** \u201cPuts concern for others above everything\u201d hints at a caring attitude that could mitigate some teamwork issues, but the lack of explicit crew\u2011cooperation evidence leaves uncertainty.\n**Major alternatives:**\n- **Candidate\u202fB** shows strong reliability (very conscientious) and handles stress well, plus solid weather\u2011assessment and computer skills. However, \u201cmakes nasty remarks about his colleagues\u201d and a weak memory for numbers raise serious crew\u2011cooperation and safety concerns.\n- **Candidate\u202fD** demonstrates responsibility, problem\u2011solving, and concentration, but a \u201chot temper\u201d and being seen as a \u201cknow\u2011it\u2011all\u201d cast doubt on calmness and teamwork.\n- **Candidate\u202fA** excels in anticipation, complex\u2011connection insight, spatial vision, and leadership, yet there is no explicit evidence of calmness under pressure, and being a \u201cshow\u2011off\u201d and \u201cnot